1. Initial guide:

pipenv install → Creates the venv
pipenv shell → Opens the venv

pipenv install flask
set FLASK_APP=hello → It's not necessary if you create a file called app.py (it will automatically 'set FLASK_APP=app')

flask run → Runs the server
exit → Exits venv

Crear ambiente de desarrollo, para no tener que recargar el servidor cada vez que se hace un cambio.
pipenv shell
set FLASK_ENV=development
flask run
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

! To run the project on dev environment (without reloading the server after each change):
pipenv shell
set FLASK_ENV=development
flask run
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////